[
    {
        "content": "<p>There is a global notation <code>R ‚àô x</code> for <code>Submodule.span R {x}</code>. This was incredibly confusing to me looking on loogle and docgen for theorems I want because it resembles the <code>a ‚Ä¢ b</code> notation for <code>HSMul.hSMul a b</code>. Should this notation be scoped?<br>\nThe notation is defined <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/24d904ee7b3f07e1b00ac06e5e170d90fafde319/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Span/Defs.lean#L301-L301\">here</a> in <code>Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Span.Defs</code>. It has about 60 uses throughout mathlib. In contrast, <code>span {_}</code> has about 600 uses throughout mathlib.</p>",
        "id": 571084835,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769793680
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note there was previous discussion to make it use the same symbol as hSMul, but I assume that would have been even more confusing</p>",
        "id": 571086498,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1769794167
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if it gets scoped, people looking at docgen won't be confused anymore <span aria-label=\"tear\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f972\" role=\"img\" title=\"tear\">:tear:</span></p>",
        "id": 571101311,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1769798950
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>not a bug, but a feature</p>",
        "id": 571101387,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1769798969
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would vote to remove this notation.</p>",
        "id": 571179777,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1769851028
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not only does it resemble ‚Ä¢, but it also resembles the notation (R ¬∑ x) for partially applied functions. I also vote remove.</p>",
        "id": 571179993,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hern√°ndez",
        "timestamp": 1769851221
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How about replacing it instead of removing? Perhaps adding a subscript <code>s</code> or <code>sp</code> for span?</p>",
        "id": 571194153,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1769863927
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I find the non-notation <code>span R {x}</code> already quite short and clear and closer to the paper maths <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{span}_R(x)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">span</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2342em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4559em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2441em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> than any notaton could be.</p>",
        "id": 571241677,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1769904250
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we remove this notation, it would be nice to \"deprecate\" it first (make it issue a deprecation warning and don't generate a delaborator from it).</p>",
        "id": 571241891,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1769904406
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"459227\">Violeta Hern√°ndez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/global.20notation.20for.20linear.20span.20of.20singleton/near/571179993\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Not only does it resemble ‚Ä¢, but it also resembles the notation (R ¬∑ x) for partially applied functions. I also vote remove.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Perhaps also worth mentioning that the span notation was invented before this function notation existed, and so this was not considered originally.</p>",
        "id": 571258019,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1769923945
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(by <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"260507\">@Heather Macbeth</span> in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/pull/5538\">!3#5538</a>, <a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/113488-general/topic/Notation.20for.20span/near/220745595\">#general &gt; Notation for span @ üí¨</a> )</p>",
