    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I usually write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">‚ü®</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">‚ü©</mo><mi>R</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\langle x \\rangle_R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">‚ü®</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">‚ü©</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ...</p>",
        "id": 571287665,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Stoll",
        "timestamp": 1769953178
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've never seen anyone write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Rx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span>? I usually just write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">‚ü®</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">‚ü©</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\langle x\\rangle</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">‚ü®</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">‚ü©</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 571346955,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hern√°ndez",
        "timestamp": 1770007798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it'd be nice to have notation ‚ü®a, b, c, ...‚ü© that we could reuse for span-like objects, such as <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.span#doc\">docs#Submodule.span</a> or <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Ideal.span#doc\">docs#Ideal.span</a> or <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Subgroup.closure#doc\">docs#Subgroup.closure</a>. Not sure if that'd be feasible.</p>\n<p>(using some other kind of angle brackets, since <code>‚ü®x‚ü©</code> already has a meaning in Lean)</p>",
        "id": 571347162,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hern√°ndez",
        "timestamp": 1770007940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"459227\">Violeta Hern√°ndez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/global.20notation.20for.20linear.20span.20of.20singleton/near/571346955\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I've never seen anyone write <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Rx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>AFAIK <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Z/n\\Z</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span></span></span></span> is a pretty common notation for <code>ZMod n</code>, and the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n\\Z</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span></span></span></span> represents the span of <code>n</code> in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Z</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span></span></span></span>. Though I guess that's <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">xR</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span> rather than <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Rx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span>.<br>\nAlso <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"113489\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Stating.20the.20theorem.20that.20no.20ring.20isomorphism.20.202Z.20and.203Z/with/562257132\">#new members &gt; Stating the theorem that no ring isomorphism  2Z and 3Z</a> is about the use of that notation in \"Abstract Algebra by Dummit and Foote\".</p>",
        "id": 571348554,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1770008946
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, but that's <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">xR</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span> rather than <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Rx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span> isn't it</p>",
